Class NetworkFailurePlugin

java.lang.Object
  CytoscapePlugin
      NetworkFailurePackage.NetworkFailurePlugin

public class NetworkFailurePlugin
extends CytoscapePlugin

Main plugin class that contains most of the application logic. Roughly represents the Controller in the MVC model (where the View are the panel classes and the model resides within Cytoscape).

Method Detail

getFailureNodesWithRemoval

public int[] getFailureNodesWithRemoval(int removeN,
                                        int iterations)
Calculates the number of failure points with removeN randomly removed nodes for iterations which are saved in an int array that is returned.

Parameters:
removeN - The number of nodes to randomly remove (i.e., mark as not transversible by the iterateNetwork() method) from the network. It is ensured that these are never failure nodes.
iterations - The number of times to repeat random node removal.
Returns:
An array of size iterations filled with the number of failure nodes found when removeN nodes were randomly removed.

getFailureNodes

public int[] getFailureNodes(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> removeArrayIndices)
Checks every node if it is essential for the network to be connected (i.e., the node is a failure node). In each step, the network is prepared by setting all removed nodes (incl. the one that is currently examined) to be iteration-path blocking and the iteration is then started with a node that is known exist. All nodes that have their essentiality flag switched on are then added to an array that is returned.

Parameters:
removeArrayIndices - An ArrayList of Integers (indices of the nodeIndices array) that should be considered as removed from the network, i.e. are not transversible by iterateNetwork(). An empty list can also be supplied and means that no nodes are removed.
Returns:
An array of node indices that were determined to be failure points.

iterateNetwork

private void iterateNetwork(int curArrayIndex,
                            boolean[] nodeReachable)
Called once using a starting node and then iterates through the rest of the network recursively, visiting all the nodes that are connected to the one where the method started via a valid path. Connections (edges) are always followed when they point downstream or are undirected.

Parameters:
curArrayIndex - The element in nodeIndices where the recursive iteration is currently at.
nodeReachable - An array that holds true for nodes that were (1) already visited or (2) marked to be deleted and false otherwise. Each array position corresponds to the same position in nodeIndices and the node indices at nodeIndices[position].
